1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:01,602
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,602 --> 00:00:03,037
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,371 --> 00:00:05,806
(Episode 43)

4
00:00:06,138 --> 00:00:08,041
I got severe meningitis...

5
00:00:08,390 --> 00:00:10,444
before being adopted by a French family,

6
00:00:11,230 --> 00:00:12,880
and I lost all my memories.

7
00:00:13,230 --> 00:00:14,448
Goodness...

8
00:00:19,709 --> 00:00:22,756
Excuse me, but...

9
00:00:23,892 --> 00:00:25,292
Could I see your calf?

10
00:00:26,430 --> 00:00:27,430
Sorry?

11
00:00:27,730 --> 00:00:30,397
There's something
I absolutely need to check.

12
00:00:39,230 --> 00:00:41,709
Why is it raining
like it's the monsoon season already?

13
00:00:45,430 --> 00:00:48,716
Every time it rains,
my calf aches so much.

14
00:01:07,301 --> 00:01:09,163
- Yeon Sun!
- Mom!

15
00:01:09,163 --> 00:01:10,163
Yeon Sun.

16
00:01:11,330 --> 00:01:12,472
- What should we do?
- Yeon Sun.

17
00:02:04,049 --> 00:02:05,092
What's wrong?

18
00:02:08,428 --> 00:02:09,428
Am I...

19
00:02:10,830 --> 00:02:12,899
not your daughter?

20
00:02:16,576 --> 00:02:19,006
I really thought
I'd find my mom this time.

21
00:02:19,730 --> 00:02:21,208
I really thought I would.

22
00:02:23,330 --> 00:02:26,030
So did I.

23
00:02:34,530 --> 00:02:35,563
What's wrong, Yeong Hwa?

24
00:02:39,663 --> 00:02:41,662
Is she really Yeon Sun?

25
00:03:05,289 --> 00:03:07,816
What happened?
Was she really your daughter?

26
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:10,730
- Take her inside.
- Yes, sir.

27
00:03:19,329 --> 00:03:21,168
Looks like it wasn't her.

28
00:03:22,930 --> 00:03:24,371
How pitiful.

29
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:31,263
Is that really
the face of someone who feels sorry?

30
00:03:31,263 --> 00:03:32,263
Excuse me?

31
00:03:33,028 --> 00:03:35,114
What's wrong with my face?

32
00:03:35,830 --> 00:03:38,819
You look absolutely thrilled.

33
00:03:41,863 --> 00:03:43,190
Seriously, that guy...

34
00:03:47,535 --> 00:03:50,630
I'm sorry. I was too hasty.

35
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:52,996
Given all the circumstances,

36
00:03:52,996 --> 00:03:55,102
I jumped to the conclusion
that she might be the same person.

37
00:03:55,830 --> 00:03:59,173
This isn't your fault,
so don't blame yourself too much.

38
00:03:59,863 --> 00:04:00,874
You worked hard.

39
00:04:01,330 --> 00:04:02,830
Yes, then...

40
00:04:12,130 --> 00:04:13,286
Yeong Hwa.

41
00:04:14,263 --> 00:04:18,058
I really thought...

42
00:04:18,763 --> 00:04:21,830
I'd meet her this time.

43
00:04:24,449 --> 00:04:26,649
Where could my Yeon Sun be?

44
00:04:28,030 --> 00:04:33,207
Honey, please find my Yeon Sun.

45
00:04:33,663 --> 00:04:34,708
Please.

46
00:04:41,063 --> 00:04:42,596
What happened, Mr. Seo?

47
00:04:43,330 --> 00:04:45,986
Was the person you met a fraud?

48
00:04:47,530 --> 00:04:48,530
Gwon Sik,

49
00:04:49,963 --> 00:04:52,125
that's not how you treat people.

50
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:55,729
How could you keep it hidden
even from your wife?

51
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:58,499
Only Jeong Ran would put up with that.
If it were me...

52
00:04:59,009 --> 00:05:00,166
I'll be leaving now.

53
00:05:13,249 --> 00:05:14,982
She must've been so disappointed.

54
00:05:31,663 --> 00:05:33,500
Honey, it was a bust.

55
00:05:34,230 --> 00:05:37,771
A bust? See? What did I tell you?

56
00:05:37,771 --> 00:05:39,930
You have to stay positive, okay?

57
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:42,476
In the end,
things turned out exactly like I said.

58
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:46,446
Right, so how's Mother doing now?

59
00:05:47,082 --> 00:05:48,915
She's crying her eyes out.

60
00:05:48,915 --> 00:05:51,963
Of course she is.
She went there with such high hopes.

61
00:05:51,963 --> 00:05:53,520
My goodness.

62
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:57,230
Honey, my Crystal, I'm busy right now,
so I'm hanging up.

63
00:05:57,730 --> 00:05:58,859
I'll be home early.

64
00:06:04,063 --> 00:06:07,063
These are the candidate sites
for Team One's project.

65
00:06:08,530 --> 00:06:13,059
Really? You work at lightning speed.

66
00:06:13,389 --> 00:06:15,208
Nice. All right then.

67
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:17,544
Okay.

68
00:06:19,530 --> 00:06:23,016
Mr. Cho, I'm in a great mood today.

69
00:06:23,016 --> 00:06:26,119
Should we go somewhere nice
and have lunch together?

70
00:06:26,686 --> 00:06:28,829
No, I brought lunch from home.

71
00:06:29,630 --> 00:06:31,591
Lunch? Sounds good.

72
00:06:31,591 --> 00:06:33,260
Is there anything for me?

73
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:35,230
Excuse me?

74
00:06:35,463 --> 00:06:37,863
I'm kidding. I was joking.

75
00:06:38,162 --> 00:06:39,162
You scare too easily.

76
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:43,704
Let's see,
then who should I share this joy with?

77
00:06:46,463 --> 00:06:49,563
Hey, Min Ho. It's Dad.
Let's have lunch together.

78
00:06:51,363 --> 00:06:53,914
What? With Gyeol too?

79
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:55,448
Come on...

80
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:02,369
Of course, sounds great. Sure.

81
00:07:05,063 --> 00:07:06,063
Then I'll be leaving.

82
00:07:06,326 --> 00:07:08,862
All right, enjoy your lunch.

83
00:07:15,730 --> 00:07:17,070
Yes!

84
00:07:18,636 --> 00:07:20,703
I finally protected my precious assets.

85
00:07:21,763 --> 00:07:23,410
I really have to be careful.

86
00:07:34,030 --> 00:07:36,256
It's lunchtime.
Aren't you all going out to eat?

87
00:07:36,730 --> 00:07:37,730
Ji Hun, what are you having?

88
00:07:37,730 --> 00:07:38,730
Good question.

89
00:07:40,630 --> 00:07:44,364
Team Manager Ko,
the CEO wants to have lunch with us.

90
00:07:44,364 --> 00:07:45,632
What? The CEO?

91
00:07:51,330 --> 00:07:52,806
I don't think I can make it.

92
00:07:53,030 --> 00:07:54,474
Why not? Do you already have plans?

93
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:56,643
No, I brought lunch from home.

94
00:07:57,030 --> 00:07:58,111
What? Lunch?

95
00:07:59,330 --> 00:08:02,530
I'm staying at a boarding house,
and they packed it for me today.

96
00:08:03,202 --> 00:08:06,586
Boarding houses still pack lunches
these days?

97
00:08:07,030 --> 00:08:09,630
Well, you don't have to eat it
if you don't want to.

98
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:12,859
No, I'll eat my lunchbox.
You go ahead without me.

99
00:08:13,563 --> 00:08:15,862
All right then.
Enjoy your meals, everyone.

100
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:20,367
Right, Manager Seo,
come to my office for a moment.

101
00:08:20,863 --> 00:08:22,102
Yes, understood.

102
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:25,030
Then should we head to the cafeteria?

103
00:08:25,363 --> 00:08:28,408
If we're going, let's go now.
I hate long lines.

104
00:08:29,063 --> 00:08:30,644
Ms. Cho, you're coming too, right?

105
00:08:31,063 --> 00:08:34,614
Sorry? I'm not really hungry.

106
00:08:38,930 --> 00:08:40,130
I said no.

107
00:08:40,130 --> 00:08:42,422
Why'd she have to pack me lunch
and make things awkward?

108
00:08:42,863 --> 00:08:45,359
So where should we eat?

109
00:08:45,930 --> 00:08:48,330
It's been raining since morning.
Where else?

110
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:49,530
We'll eat in the pantry.

111
00:08:50,096 --> 00:08:52,231
You didn't know?
The rain stopped a while ago.

112
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,501
Want to go on a picnic?

113
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:56,730
What? A picnic?

114
00:08:57,463 --> 00:08:59,973
I wanted to apologize.

115
00:09:01,330 --> 00:09:03,276
About yesterday,
in front of the bindaetteok place...

116
00:09:03,763 --> 00:09:07,180
No, I don't think you owe me an apology.

117
00:09:07,963 --> 00:09:12,330
I just got too emotional yesterday
and made a mistake.

118
00:09:13,230 --> 00:09:14,230
I'm really sorry.

119
00:09:14,902 --> 00:09:16,322
I don't know what you're talking about,

120
00:09:16,663 --> 00:09:19,030
but I don't remember anything,
so don't worry about it.

121
00:09:19,430 --> 00:09:20,430
I'll get going.

122
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:27,100
She doesn't even want to think about it?

123
00:09:28,330 --> 00:09:29,836
I don't think that's how it was.

124
00:09:30,889 --> 00:09:31,889
Seung Ri.

125
00:09:33,430 --> 00:09:35,308
I'm okay with being hurt,

126
00:09:37,130 --> 00:09:39,030
but I can't bear
to see you hurting anymore.

127
00:09:41,463 --> 00:09:43,363
Please, stop this, okay?

128
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:04,530
Come on, Ko Min Ho. Keep it together.

129
00:10:05,830 --> 00:10:08,830
She asked me out for drinks first.

130
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:11,645
That's already half a success, yes.

131
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:13,630
Okay, I can do this.

132
00:10:25,030 --> 00:10:28,230
Your mother's cooking
is the second best in the world.

133
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:31,230
Second best? Then what's first?

134
00:10:31,930 --> 00:10:33,163
Obviously my grandma's cooking.

135
00:10:33,163 --> 00:10:35,463
Then why did you move out,

136
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:38,030
leaving behind the best home-cooked meals
in the world?

137
00:10:39,663 --> 00:10:40,663
The last rolled omelet.

138
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:44,210
I was just about to grab that.

139
00:10:44,562 --> 00:10:46,146
No one can resist the last rolled omelet.

140
00:10:47,863 --> 00:10:48,948
Then let's settle it
with rock-paper-scissors.

141
00:10:49,682 --> 00:10:51,229
You're surprisingly greedy with food.

142
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:52,930
All right, let's do it.

143
00:10:56,730 --> 00:10:57,763
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

144
00:10:58,263 --> 00:10:59,263
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

145
00:11:00,730 --> 00:11:01,730
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

146
00:11:06,163 --> 00:11:07,163
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

147
00:11:08,063 --> 00:11:10,063
- What kind of scene is that?
- Rock, paper, scissors.

148
00:11:10,063 --> 00:11:12,263
- Those two are dating.
- Again.

149
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:15,263
- What? No way.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

150
00:11:15,263 --> 00:11:17,130
Hey, Gyeol dating? Come on.

151
00:11:17,377 --> 00:11:20,280
Look at them.
If that's not dating, what is?

152
00:11:21,147 --> 00:11:23,082
You're right.

153
00:11:23,863 --> 00:11:27,130
Seriously, Gyeol had that side to him?

154
00:11:27,130 --> 00:11:29,122
Just pretend you didn't see anything.

155
00:11:29,122 --> 00:11:31,224
Why?
The most entertaining things in life...

156
00:11:31,224 --> 00:11:33,393
are watching fires, fights, and romance.

157
00:11:33,393 --> 00:11:34,827
Honestly, Dad.

158
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,130
By the way, is there good news?

159
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:39,299
Why do you keep smiling like that?

160
00:11:41,063 --> 00:11:42,963
I protected my precious assets today.

161
00:11:43,230 --> 00:11:45,730
And you don't have to split things
into fractions of fractions anymore.

162
00:11:45,962 --> 00:11:47,762
What? What do you mean by that?

163
00:11:48,007 --> 00:11:49,409
Just something like that.

164
00:11:49,409 --> 00:11:51,630
What do you mean, "something like that?"
Dad!

165
00:11:52,530 --> 00:11:54,630
The last rolled omelet
is always the best one.

166
00:11:55,930 --> 00:11:58,418
- I let you have it, you know.
- What?

167
00:12:03,636 --> 00:12:05,458
You don't think they saw us, do you?

168
00:12:05,919 --> 00:12:06,919
So what if they did?

169
00:12:08,309 --> 00:12:09,962
I don't get it.

170
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:12,865
The Chief is really close
with his father...

171
00:12:15,469 --> 00:12:17,370
We've got an intense meeting
this afternoon, so brace yourself.

172
00:12:17,763 --> 00:12:18,830
Okay.

173
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:22,163
I'll head up first. Come up after a bit.

174
00:12:22,963 --> 00:12:26,012
What? Why do we need a time gap?
Let's go together.

175
00:12:26,713 --> 00:12:28,430
Come later. I told you to wait.

176
00:12:28,430 --> 00:12:29,830
Did we commit a crime or something?

177
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:36,163
Hey, where are you coming back from?

178
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:38,230
The Chairman's house.

179
00:12:40,809 --> 00:12:42,762
But why do you look so down?

180
00:12:43,398 --> 00:12:45,365
CEO Ko looked pretty upbeat.

181
00:12:47,449 --> 00:12:50,770
Is this about that person
their family was looking for?

182
00:12:51,273 --> 00:12:54,073
It wasn't her. They met this morning.

183
00:12:54,262 --> 00:12:55,262
Really?

184
00:12:55,696 --> 00:12:58,478
Then does that mean
CEO Ko was hoping they wouldn't find her?

185
00:12:59,863 --> 00:13:01,014
I guess so.

186
00:13:02,363 --> 00:13:04,230
Seriously, who could it be?

187
00:13:04,930 --> 00:13:06,386
Right, you haven't had lunch yet,
have you?

188
00:13:06,930 --> 00:13:08,630
I packed a lunch. Let's eat together.

189
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:11,930
My wife always cooks way too much food.

190
00:13:12,663 --> 00:13:14,461
I don't know if I should eat it too.

191
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:16,330
Your wife made it with care.

192
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:18,830
Listen to yourself.

193
00:13:19,830 --> 00:13:20,963
Come on, eat with me.

194
00:13:28,155 --> 00:13:29,230
Hello.

195
00:13:29,230 --> 00:13:30,830
Yu Jeong Ran, what brings you here?

196
00:13:31,463 --> 00:13:33,013
I managed to find the place.

197
00:13:33,382 --> 00:13:36,839
I found my way thanks to the business card
you gave me at the dance studio.

198
00:13:37,409 --> 00:13:40,076
I hope I'm not being rude
by dropping by like this.

199
00:13:40,076 --> 00:13:42,030
- Not at all. Please sit.
- Thank you.

200
00:13:44,529 --> 00:13:47,060
Are all those certificates yours,
Kang Yeon Ja?

201
00:13:47,949 --> 00:13:50,229
They're just hobbies.

202
00:13:51,619 --> 00:13:53,929
At our age,
earning certificates as a hobby...

203
00:13:53,930 --> 00:13:55,230
isn't exactly easy.

204
00:13:55,836 --> 00:13:57,103
That's impressive.

205
00:13:57,330 --> 00:13:58,530
- It's nothing.
- Well...

206
00:13:59,330 --> 00:14:01,830
Things were so hectic that day...

207
00:14:01,830 --> 00:14:04,411
I was disappointed
we couldn't really talk properly.

208
00:14:05,063 --> 00:14:07,530
Our husbands have apparently been
best friends for years.

209
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:10,263
And for us to meet
at the dance studio like that,

210
00:14:10,263 --> 00:14:12,251
it really feels like fate.

211
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:15,488
I know.
For a coincidence, it's pretty remarkable.

212
00:14:15,488 --> 00:14:16,856
So what I want to say is...

213
00:14:17,863 --> 00:14:19,959
Do you want to be friends?

214
00:14:20,596 --> 00:14:23,029
Excuse me? Friends?

215
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:26,766
Yes. Somehow, from the moment we met,

216
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:30,530
I had a feeling
we'd get along really well.

217
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,063
I see...

218
00:14:34,063 --> 00:14:35,463
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

219
00:14:41,530 --> 00:14:42,530
Hey, Eun Hyeong.

220
00:14:43,430 --> 00:14:47,087
About that cheap rental place
you mentioned before...

221
00:14:47,763 --> 00:14:49,330
Do you think there's anywhere decent?

222
00:14:49,330 --> 00:14:51,530
There is one place available,

223
00:14:51,930 --> 00:14:53,230
but it's an older villa apartment,

224
00:14:53,730 --> 00:14:55,995
and it's also pretty far
from Bit Na's kindergarten.

225
00:14:56,148 --> 00:14:57,363
Would that be okay?

226
00:14:57,363 --> 00:14:58,732
Don't worry about that.

227
00:14:59,530 --> 00:15:02,963
I'll talk it over with Ji Seon
and probably go see it tomorrow.

228
00:15:04,263 --> 00:15:06,239
Okay. Goodbye.

229
00:15:07,863 --> 00:15:09,108
Are we moving?

230
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:11,109
Probably.

231
00:15:13,413 --> 00:15:14,830
(ALPHA AI Global Algorithm Fund)

232
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:16,049
I can't believe it!

233
00:15:16,430 --> 00:15:20,186
I invested 50,000 from the deposit,
and it's already 70,000?

234
00:15:21,387 --> 00:15:24,562
So it's true!
Money really does make money.

235
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:28,230
Honey, Mother said...

236
00:15:28,763 --> 00:15:30,730
there's a cheap villa available,

237
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:33,133
though it's a bit far
from this neighborhood.

238
00:15:33,330 --> 00:15:34,663
Do you think
we could go see it together tomorrow?

239
00:15:35,269 --> 00:15:37,603
Honey, we don't have to move.

240
00:15:38,130 --> 00:15:40,907
Actually,
should we move to an even bigger place?

241
00:15:41,082 --> 00:15:42,542
What are you talking about?

242
00:15:43,489 --> 00:15:48,289
You took out the deposit from this house
and invested it?

243
00:15:48,628 --> 00:15:50,583
Yeah. Look.

244
00:15:51,730 --> 00:15:55,555
I invested 50,000 dollars,
and now it's 70,000 dollars.

245
00:15:55,723 --> 00:15:57,623
- What? 70,000 dollars?
- Yeah.

246
00:15:58,363 --> 00:16:01,093
Mom, does that mean
the five apples turned into seven apples?

247
00:16:01,093 --> 00:16:04,263
What? Apples? Yeah, apples.

248
00:16:04,830 --> 00:16:08,134
Bit Na,
the five apples turned into seven apples.

249
00:16:10,189 --> 00:16:13,639
You made 20,000 dollars that easily
in just a week?

250
00:16:14,236 --> 00:16:16,676
That's more than I make
working an entire year.

251
00:16:17,169 --> 00:16:18,643
Exactly.

252
00:16:19,522 --> 00:16:22,689
The person who introduced me to this
was that junior I met before.

253
00:16:23,130 --> 00:16:25,785
Apparently, her mother-in-law makes money
the same way.

254
00:16:26,063 --> 00:16:29,163
Honey,
if it already went up by 20,000 dollars,

255
00:16:29,502 --> 00:16:32,057
that's exactly enough to cover
the increased deposit for this house.

256
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:35,583
Let's pull the money out
and renew the lease first.

257
00:16:35,583 --> 00:16:37,296
What if the value drops?

258
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:41,334
Why are you so timid?

259
00:16:41,334 --> 00:16:45,063
When it's rising like this,
you have to invest even more aggressively.

260
00:16:45,330 --> 00:16:46,573
A beast's heart.

261
00:16:48,030 --> 00:16:51,130
That's the basic principle of investing.

262
00:16:51,930 --> 00:16:54,030
I don't care about that.

263
00:16:54,322 --> 00:16:56,722
We need to secure this house first
so we don't have to move.

264
00:16:57,689 --> 00:16:59,554
I feel like
I'm about to have a heart attack. Please.

265
00:17:00,930 --> 00:17:03,689
Fine. I'll do it. Seriously.

266
00:17:07,059 --> 00:17:09,362
(Withdrawal failed)

267
00:17:09,362 --> 00:17:10,363
What is this?

268
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:12,630
(Withdrawals are temporarily restricted
due to verification.)

269
00:17:12,630 --> 00:17:14,200
What's wrong, honey?

270
00:17:17,837 --> 00:17:18,840
(Group Chat)

271
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:21,641
(You can no longer participate.)

272
00:17:22,302 --> 00:17:24,342
Wait, do you think
you got scammed or something...

273
00:17:25,330 --> 00:17:28,081
No way. That can't be it.

274
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:30,517
I'll try calling my junior.

275
00:17:33,363 --> 00:17:35,288
The phone is turned off.
Please leave a message...

276
00:17:35,863 --> 00:17:38,824
Mom, what's wrong?
Did the apples disappear?

277
00:17:41,563 --> 00:17:42,563
Honey!

278
00:17:42,863 --> 00:17:44,464
- Mom!
- Honey, where are you going?

279
00:17:44,663 --> 00:17:45,663
- Mom!
- Honey!

280
00:17:46,763 --> 00:17:49,469
That day must've upset you.

281
00:17:50,130 --> 00:17:53,773
Just let it go.
Su Jeong has always been like that.

282
00:17:54,362 --> 00:17:55,362
I'm okay.

283
00:17:56,330 --> 00:17:58,963
By the way, you're impressive.

284
00:17:58,963 --> 00:18:00,430
How do you do that every day?

285
00:18:00,430 --> 00:18:03,783
Our family owes the Chairman's family
a huge debt.

286
00:18:04,363 --> 00:18:05,797
Even if it bothers me,

287
00:18:05,797 --> 00:18:08,253
I just think of it as repaying a favor
and let it go.

288
00:18:09,963 --> 00:18:13,730
Right, what happened
with the person they found that day?

289
00:18:14,175 --> 00:18:15,294
I don't know.

290
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:19,799
As you can tell, my husband's the type
who keeps his mouth shut tight.

291
00:18:20,043 --> 00:18:22,843
But who exactly were they looking for?

292
00:18:23,163 --> 00:18:25,071
The atmosphere was really tense.

293
00:18:26,703 --> 00:18:28,941
I don't know if I should even say this...

294
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:31,477
Apparently, it was Madam's daughter.

295
00:18:32,063 --> 00:18:34,894
What? Madam, as in...

296
00:18:35,463 --> 00:18:36,916
The CEO's mother?

297
00:18:36,916 --> 00:18:37,916
Yes.

298
00:18:38,930 --> 00:18:41,784
But CEO Ko is supposed to be
the Chairman's only child.

299
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:44,912
I have no idea what happened.

300
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:48,594
Maybe she had a child
before marrying the Chairman or something.

301
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:50,630
Really?

302
00:18:51,682 --> 00:18:53,649
I don't know if this will comfort you...

303
00:18:54,563 --> 00:18:56,836
but a child betraying their mother...

304
00:18:58,410 --> 00:19:00,710
is probably still better than...

305
00:19:02,095 --> 00:19:03,843
a mother betraying her child.

306
00:19:06,930 --> 00:19:08,730
A child betrayed by their mother...

307
00:19:09,830 --> 00:19:13,119
is practically abandoned
by the whole world.

308
00:19:14,430 --> 00:19:16,630
Imagine your child carrying that wound...

309
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:19,292
for their entire life.

310
00:19:21,230 --> 00:19:22,863
Parents always hurt more...

311
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:26,432
over their child's pain than their own.

312
00:19:28,823 --> 00:19:31,871
By the way, how do you...

313
00:19:32,263 --> 00:19:33,463
and Madam know each other?

314
00:19:34,359 --> 00:19:36,375
I wouldn't really say we know each other.

315
00:19:37,182 --> 00:19:39,763
We just happened to meet once before.

316
00:19:39,763 --> 00:19:41,648
Let's meet often from now on.

317
00:19:42,063 --> 00:19:43,363
Come visit my house too.

318
00:19:46,486 --> 00:19:47,486
(Studio Usage Rules)

319
00:19:47,486 --> 00:19:50,829
Rule number one.
We agreed on the schedule, right?

320
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:53,630
Okay. Day, you. Night, me.

321
00:19:53,630 --> 00:19:56,630
What did you just say?

322
00:19:56,630 --> 00:19:58,197
What are you thinking?

323
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:01,400
Day is yours, night is mine.
"Day, you. Night, me."

324
00:20:03,830 --> 00:20:06,530
If you violate the schedule,
the penalty is 30 dollars per hour.

325
00:20:07,330 --> 00:20:08,775
Deal. Rule number two.

326
00:20:08,775 --> 00:20:11,063
If you bring outsiders in
without the other person's consent,

327
00:20:11,063 --> 00:20:13,112
you lose access to the studio
for 24 hours.

328
00:20:13,446 --> 00:20:15,530
Fine. It's not like I can only meet people
in the studio.

329
00:20:15,530 --> 00:20:17,416
Third, we clean every other day.

330
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:19,229
I clean on odd-numbered days,
you clean on even-numbered days.

331
00:20:19,663 --> 00:20:22,488
It's not "you." It's Seo Seung Wu.

332
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:24,430
Let me add one more rule.

333
00:20:24,930 --> 00:20:25,930
Well...

334
00:20:26,663 --> 00:20:29,330
Number one in the bathroom inside,
number two in the outside bathroom.

335
00:20:29,330 --> 00:20:33,333
Excuse me? So you're saying...

336
00:20:34,063 --> 00:20:35,935
don't do number two
in the studio bathroom?

337
00:20:36,863 --> 00:20:38,930
Why? It's a natural bodily function.

338
00:20:39,430 --> 00:20:42,163
Who said not to do it?
I said use the outside bathroom.

339
00:20:42,930 --> 00:20:44,210
That's about it, right?

340
00:20:45,130 --> 00:20:47,413
We'll add more rules gradually if needed.

341
00:20:47,930 --> 00:20:51,250
Print this out and put it on the wall.

342
00:20:52,530 --> 00:20:53,530
Now.

343
00:21:01,630 --> 00:21:05,398
Don't forget, she's a crazy girl.
Remember, she's a crazy girl.

344
00:21:07,363 --> 00:21:11,504
Right, could you put away
that doll you're holding?

345
00:21:11,963 --> 00:21:12,963
What?

346
00:21:13,563 --> 00:21:16,375
This is my favorite comfort doll. Why?

347
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:20,312
It oddly distracts me.

348
00:21:24,263 --> 00:21:26,819
And whenever I see this notebook...

349
00:21:32,076 --> 00:21:33,076
Hey, Hye Ji.

350
00:21:34,430 --> 00:21:35,862
What? You're coming here again?

351
00:21:37,563 --> 00:21:39,031
No, not today.

352
00:21:39,706 --> 00:21:41,230
I'm working at home tonight.

353
00:21:41,730 --> 00:21:44,303
Really? Then even better.

354
00:21:44,630 --> 00:21:46,539
- What?
- I told you.

355
00:21:46,539 --> 00:21:48,707
Mr. Seo is totally my type.

356
00:21:50,576 --> 00:21:53,492
Listen, don't ever tell him this.

357
00:21:53,936 --> 00:21:57,010
I'm going to pretend
I came because of you tonight.

358
00:21:59,163 --> 00:22:00,520
Hey! Oh Hye Ji!

359
00:22:14,483 --> 00:22:15,763
Rock, paper, scissors.

360
00:22:15,763 --> 00:22:17,002
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

361
00:22:17,230 --> 00:22:18,430
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

362
00:22:19,672 --> 00:22:21,974
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

363
00:22:21,974 --> 00:22:23,530
Yes!

364
00:22:23,530 --> 00:22:26,045
The bed is mine tonight.

365
00:22:26,045 --> 00:22:28,530
Happy? Stealing your younger sister's bed?

366
00:22:28,981 --> 00:22:31,517
Very. Just wait until you get to my age.

367
00:22:31,517 --> 00:22:33,819
Everywhere aches
when I sleep on the floor.

368
00:22:33,819 --> 00:22:36,288
Fine, dear elderly sister.

369
00:22:36,730 --> 00:22:38,491
Sleep well.

370
00:22:42,463 --> 00:22:44,863
I'm behind on my serialization,
so I'll be working late.

371
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:45,930
Sleep with an eye mask on.

372
00:22:45,930 --> 00:22:48,100
But I won't tolerate noise.

373
00:22:48,430 --> 00:22:50,937
Don't yell while writing like last time.

374
00:22:56,763 --> 00:22:58,730
What was that rock-paper-scissors thing
just now?

375
00:22:59,030 --> 00:23:00,613
Competing with your sister
over late-night snacks?

376
00:23:02,730 --> 00:23:03,963
No way.

377
00:23:03,963 --> 00:23:06,730
My sister and I have this game
we play every night.

378
00:23:07,030 --> 00:23:09,521
It's more like a desperate struggle
for survival.

379
00:23:24,163 --> 00:23:26,806
What is this? Delete it right now.

380
00:23:46,030 --> 00:23:47,093
You happy?

381
00:23:47,330 --> 00:23:49,930
Then go across to the Team Manager's room.

382
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:52,030
What are you two even doing
with just one door between you?

383
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:53,230
You're distracting me.

384
00:23:53,230 --> 00:23:54,867
How am I distracting you?

385
00:23:55,030 --> 00:23:56,463
I didn't make a sound.

386
00:23:56,663 --> 00:23:58,463
That's the loudest part.

387
00:23:58,463 --> 00:24:00,806
Haven't you heard of a silent scream?

388
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:02,530
That's ridiculous.

389
00:24:04,630 --> 00:24:06,263
Come out to the yard for a second.

390
00:24:06,263 --> 00:24:08,881
Let's have a serious discussion
about violating image rights.

391
00:24:13,221 --> 00:24:15,688
Are you really going
to the Team Manager's room?

392
00:24:15,863 --> 00:24:18,330
You think I'm crazy?
I'm just getting water.

393
00:24:26,130 --> 00:24:27,130
What's with her?

394
00:24:28,230 --> 00:24:31,063
Eun Hyeong's landlord suddenly...

395
00:24:31,063 --> 00:24:33,739
raised the deposit by 20,000 dollars,
so they have to move.

396
00:24:33,976 --> 00:24:34,976
What?

397
00:24:35,609 --> 00:24:38,110
How can they suddenly raise the deposit
that much?

398
00:24:38,342 --> 00:24:39,845
That's just how the market is these days.

399
00:24:41,462 --> 00:24:43,849
He's going with me tomorrow
to see another place.

400
00:24:44,418 --> 00:24:45,951
I'm worried about Bit Na's mom.

401
00:24:46,054 --> 00:24:48,654
Why? Is the place in bad condition?

402
00:24:49,263 --> 00:24:51,530
She wasn't satisfied
with the current place,

403
00:24:52,130 --> 00:24:54,026
and the new one is much worse.

404
00:24:56,216 --> 00:24:58,430
When they got married,

405
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:01,630
I wish we could've at least helped them
get a place, even if it was a stretch.

406
00:25:01,630 --> 00:25:05,638
It's hard enough earning money,
paying rent, and covering living expenses.

407
00:25:06,063 --> 00:25:08,541
Even when we offered to help
with the deposit, Eun Hyeong refused.

408
00:25:09,463 --> 00:25:11,110
He said we'd already done enough...

409
00:25:11,330 --> 00:25:13,679
by putting him through school.

410
00:25:16,830 --> 00:25:18,863
What was that sound just now?

411
00:25:19,451 --> 00:25:22,021
What? I don't know.

412
00:25:22,930 --> 00:25:24,056
I'll go check.

413
00:25:26,802 --> 00:25:29,428
Delete it right now.
Delete it in front of me.

414
00:25:29,830 --> 00:25:30,830
Nope.

415
00:25:32,230 --> 00:25:34,130
Keeping someone else's photo
without permission...

416
00:25:34,130 --> 00:25:35,163
is a violation of image rights.

417
00:25:35,163 --> 00:25:36,930
And if it gets leaked,

418
00:25:36,930 --> 00:25:38,637
it's also a violation
of the information network law.

419
00:25:38,637 --> 00:25:41,607
Really? Then let's check your phone too.

420
00:25:41,930 --> 00:25:44,963
You still have that picture of me
with a card stuck to my forehead.

421
00:25:44,963 --> 00:25:46,730
Why are we talking about my phone now?

422
00:25:46,730 --> 00:25:48,730
- Open it. You still have it.
- No.

423
00:25:48,730 --> 00:25:50,030
I don't.

424
00:26:05,097 --> 00:26:07,032
The kids didn't lock the door.

425
00:26:15,263 --> 00:26:16,976
Did you hear the door lock just now?

426
00:26:17,330 --> 00:26:19,311
Really? I didn't...

427
00:26:25,030 --> 00:26:26,952
What do we do? The door's locked.

428
00:26:27,875 --> 00:26:29,421
Don't you have a key?

429
00:26:29,621 --> 00:26:30,956
Of course not.

430
00:26:31,430 --> 00:26:33,526
I'll ask Eun Nim to open it
since she's still awake.

431
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:43,001
(Eun Ae)

432
00:26:45,130 --> 00:26:46,672
Eun Nim isn't answering either.

433
00:26:47,039 --> 00:26:48,740
Mom and Dad are probably asleep already.

434
00:26:54,530 --> 00:26:57,130
Cho Eun Ae? Team Manager Ko?

435
00:27:04,889 --> 00:27:05,889
Dad.

436
00:27:10,630 --> 00:27:12,530
Honey, on your way back from exercising,
could you grab some milk...

437
00:27:14,930 --> 00:27:16,330
What are you all doing out here
so early in the morning?

438
00:27:16,330 --> 00:27:17,963
Well...

439
00:27:25,744 --> 00:27:26,744
Eun Hyeong.

440
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:57,943
(Our Happy Days)

441
00:27:57,976 --> 00:28:00,279
I was wondering if you could watch Bit Na
for a few days.

442
00:28:00,279 --> 00:28:01,714
Sure, that's no problem.

443
00:28:03,582 --> 00:28:05,130
There isn't some other problem, is there?

444
00:28:05,330 --> 00:28:06,886
I invested
because I trusted what you said!

445
00:28:07,330 --> 00:28:09,263
What on earth happened?

446
00:28:09,263 --> 00:28:11,223
What am I supposed to do now?

447
00:28:11,363 --> 00:28:13,392
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
do you like Team Manager Ko?

448
00:28:13,392 --> 00:28:17,529
Do I have any reason
to answer that question?

449
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:19,431
Please take good care of my Gyeol.

450
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,935
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
